node.text:
Samara and I shared such a sweet little moment today — or so I thought! 

While I was in the playpen snapping pics of the kittens, she woke up and moseyed on over to me. She raised her head, half-climbed my knee, and then paused. She studied my face and camera, so curious as to what I was doing. There she stayed, frozen in place while I turned my focus to her and began taking photos. I thought, "This is so cool! Samara is really interested in what I'm doing and is posing for my shots!" I continued to snap as many pics as I could. 

Then I felt an all too familiar sensation combination. Wet warmth.

I looked down to discover a river of piss coming from between her legs - all over my knee and the blanket. As soon as she was done, she immediately dislodged her claws and stumbled back over to fall fast asleep in the pile of her siblings. And that's how I became a litterbox today. 

If you look closely, you'll notice an unmistakable glisten in the photo just moments before it reached me. ✨

node.text:
THIS IS NOT A DRILL

Among the *7* new babies we got today, 2 of them are tricolor. So you know how I’m feeling right now. 🥰🥰🥰🥰

Big props to @me0wsages for taking care of them for the past two weeks while they quarantined! She did a wonderful job and they are all so happy & healthy.

If you need me, you can find me in the nursery with my head stuffed in the incubator. 🙃
